name: NEIC, USGS, Major quakes of magnitude 4.5 or more in the World and 2.5 or more in the U.S from May 03 to May 10 2010, World, 2010
description:
The point shapefile shows locations of major earthquakes of magnitude 4.5 or more across the world and 2.5 or more in the U.S. Northern Sumatra had 7.2 magnitude quake but did not cause any damage or generate tsunami.
For the first time in last several weeks, the total number of quakes is less than 300.
